从历史上看，以色列依靠外部进口来满足其大部分能源需求，2009年在能源产品进口上的支出相当于其国内生产总值的5%以上。<ref name="gas1">{{cite news |title=Gas discovery tempers Israeli recession blues |first=Amotz |last=Asa-El |url=http://articles.marketwatch.com/2009-01-27/news/30797823_1_gas-discovery-delek-group-natural-gas/2 |newspaper=MarketWatch |date=27 January 2009 |accessdate=17 October 2012 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130128053526/http://articles.marketwatch.com/2009-01-27/news/30797823_1_gas-discovery-delek-group-natural-gas/2 |archivedate=2013-01-28 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>交通部门主要依靠汽油和柴油，而电力生产的大部分是使用进口煤炭。截至2013年，以色列每年进口大约1亿桶石油。<ref>[https://www.eia.gov/beta/international/country.cfm?iso=ISR Israel's Key Energy Statistics] {{Wayback|url=https://www.eia.gov/beta/international/country.cfm?iso=ISR |date=20170731035659 }} - [[Energy_Information_Administration|Energy Information Administration]] site</ref>以色列的原油储量微不足道，但其国内的天然气资源却从2009年开始被大量发现。此前，以色列进行了数十年不成功的勘探。<ref name=Gas1/><ref name=eiarpt>{{cite web|title=Oil and natural gas in the Eastern Mediterranean region (summer 2013 report)|publisher=[[Energy_Information_Administration|U.S. Energy Information Administration]]|date=15 August 2013|url=http://www.eia.gov/countries/regions-topics.cfm?fips=EM|accessdate=24 August 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901220817/http://www.eia.gov/countries/regions-topics.cfm?fips=EM|archivedate=2013-09-01|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="gas6">{{cite news |first=Charles |last=Levinson |author2=Chazan, Guy |title=Big Gas Find Sparks a Frenzy in Israel |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204204004576049842786766586 |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=30 December 2010 |accessdate=1 January 2011 |archive-date=2019-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523213806/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970204204004576049842786766586 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="gas10">{{cite news |last=Bar-Eli |first=Avi |title=400 Drills in 60 Years: Is there Oil in Israel? |url=http://www.themarker.com/markets/1.631559 |accessdate=27 April 2011 |newspaper=[[TheMarker|TheMarker]] |date=26 April 2011 |language=he |archive-date=2018-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106212146/https://www.themarker.com/markets/1.631559 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Udasin|first=Sharon|title=New Natural Gas Wealth Means Historic Change for Israel|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/energy/2012/07/120703-israel-new-natural-gas|accessdate=25 August 2012|newspaper=[[National_Geographic_Society|National Geographic News]]|date=3 July 2012|location=part of "The Great Energy Challenge" series|archive-date=2019-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190212084120/https://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/energy/2012/07/120703-israel-new-natural-gas/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
==== 天然气 ====
直到21世纪初，以色列的天然气使用量还很少。在20世纪90年代末，由于环境、成本和资源多样化的原因，以色列的政府决定鼓励天然气的使用。然而，当时国内没有天然气来源，人们的期望是，天然气将以液化天然气的形式从海外供应，并在未来通过从埃及的管道供应。以色列电力公司计划建造几座以天然气为动力的发电厂，建立一个全国天然气分配网和一个液化天然气进口终端。

